quest_title: On increasing the reverse bias to a large value in a \(\textit{PN-}\)junction diode, current
explanation_txt: Initially on increasing the reverse voltage, very less or no current flows through diode. During this stage, depletion region goes on increasing. Once a critical voltage is crossed, charge carriers are hugely accelerated causing collision with other atoms and further generating more charge carriers (electrons and holes). This results in huge amount of current flow in reverse direction. This critical voltage is called breakdown voltage.
